        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(tts): add word-level timestamps to TTS synthesis",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Adds `wordTimestamps` to `SpeechSynthesisResult` and `TtsSynthesisResult`\n- Changes ElevenLabs provider to use the `/with-timestamps` endpoint\n- Propagates wordTimestamps through speech-provider.ts and synthesizeSpeech\n- Removes already-merged memory-core dreaming fix (was in PR #80646)\n- Fixes test to use correct import paths for current packages/speech-core layout\n- Properly types ElevenLabs timestamp response (no `as any`)\n\nCloses #80613\nReplaces #80646 (stale, conflicting)\n\nSigned-off-by: Md Mushfiqur Rahim <20mahin2020@gmail.com>\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nTo reproduce, configure an ElevenLabs API key and run:\n\n```bash\n# Start OpenClaw with ElevenLabs provider configured\n# Then send a TTS request:\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/tts \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\":\"Hello world with timestamps\",\"provider\":\"elevenlabs\"}'\n```\n\nExpected: The TTS response includes `wordTimestamps` with `characters`, `characterStartTimesSeconds`, and `characterEndTimesSeconds` arrays.\n\n> Evidence from running against a real ElevenLabs account will be added once available. The feature has been verified through:\n> - typed response parsing (no `as any`)\n> - unit test coverage for timestamp propagation\n> - CI green across all checks\n\n",
